description: Returns an array of ProtocolsListDataSummary objects.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The maximum number of objects that you want Firewall Manager to return for this request. If more objects are available, in the response, Firewall Manager provides a NextToken value that you can use in a subsequent call to get the next batch of objects. If you don't specify this, Firewall Manager returns all available objects.

nested_items.name: ListArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the specified protocols list.

nested_items.name: ListId
nested_items.description: The ID of the specified protocols list.

nested_items.name: ListName
nested_items.description: The name of the specified protocols list.

nested_items.name: ProtocolsList
nested_items.description: An array of protocols in the Firewall Manager protocols list.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If you specify a value for MaxResults in your list request, and you have more objects than the maximum, Firewall Manager returns this token in the response. You can use this token in subsequent requests to retrieve the next batch of objects.
